<refentry id='gifinfo.1'>
<refentryinfo><date>21 July 1999</date></refentryinfo>
<refmeta>
<refentrytitle>gifinfo</refentrytitle>
<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
<refmiscinfo class="source">GIFLIB</refmiscinfo>
<refmiscinfo class="manual">GIFLIB Documentation</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>
<refnamediv id='name'>
<refname>gifinfo</refname>
<refpurpose>extract information from a GIF</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>

<cmdsynopsis>
  <command>gifinfo</command>
      <arg choice='opt'>-v</arg>
      <arg choice='opt'>-f <replaceable>format string</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice='opt'>-h</arg>
      <arg rep='repeat'>
	<group><replaceable>gif-file</replaceable></group>
      </arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>

<para>Dump meta-information from a GIF as expansions of escapes in a
format string.</para>

</refsect1>
<refsect1><title>Options</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>-f format string</term>
<listitem>
<para>In the format string, certain escapes (listed below) are expanded,</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>-h</term>
<listitem>
<para>Print one line of command line help, similar to Usage above.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

<para>The escapes are as follows:</para>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>\h</term>
<listitem>
<para>Image height</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>\w</term>
<listitem>
<para>width</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>\c</term>
<listitem>
<para>Image comment.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>\f</term>
<listitem>
<para>Image file name.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</refsect1>
<refsect1><title>Author</title>

<para>Martin Edlman.</para>

</refsect1>
</refentry>
